```

## Development Rules

### 1. Component Guidelines

- Use TypeScript strictly - no `any` types
- All components must be server components by default, use "use client" only when necessary
- Follow React naming conventions (PascalCase for components)
- Use ShadCN/UI components for consistency
- Implement proper error boundaries

### 2. Styling Rules

- Use Tailwind CSS classes only - no inline styles
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use CSS Modules only for complex animations or when Tailwind is insufficient
- Implement dark mode support from start

### 3. State Management

- Use Zustand for client state management
- Keep server state in React Query/TanStack Query
- Local storage for guest cart, database for logged users
- Implement proper loading and error states

### 4. API Development

- All API routes must use TypeScript
- Implement proper error handling with status codes
- Use Zod for request/response validation
- Implement rate limiting for sensitive endpoints
- Follow RESTful conventions

### 5. Database Rules

- Use Prisma ORM exclusively
- All database operations must be through Prisma
- Implement proper migrations for schema changes
- Use environment variables for database connection

## Feature Implementation Rules

### 1. Product Management

- All product pages must use SSR/SSG for SEO
- Implement proper image optimization with next/image
- Use slug-based URLs: `/product/[slug]`
- Implement proper caching strategies

### 2. Cart System

- Persist cart in localStorage for guests
- Sync cart with database for logged users
- Implement real-time cart updates
- Support promo codes and discounts

### 3. Checkout Flow

- Multi-step checkout process
- Support guest checkout
- Integrate Stripe for payments
- Implement proper order confirmation
- Send email notifications

### 4. Authentication

- Use NextAuth.js for authentication
- Support social login (Google, Facebook)
- Implement proper session management
- Password reset functionality

### 5. Admin Panel

- Role-based access control
- CRUD operations for products
- Order management system
- Basic analytics dashboard

## Performance Requirements

### 1. Core Web Vitals

- Target Lighthouse score: 90+
- Implement proper lazy loading
- Use next/image for all images
- Implement code splitting

### 2. SEO Requirements

- Dynamic meta tags for all pages
- Open Graph tags implementation
- Structured data (JSON-LD) for products
- Clean, readable URLs

### 3. Caching Strategy

- Use ISR for product pages
- Implement proper cache headers
- CDN optimization through Vercel

## Security Rules

### 1. Authentication & Authorization

- HTTPS everywhere
- Secure session management
- Role-based access control
- Input validation with Zod

### 2. Payment Security

- Never store credit card information
- Use Stripe Elements for payment forms
- Implement proper webhook handling
- PCI compliance considerations

### 3. Data Protection

- Sanitize all user inputs
- Implement CSRF protection
- Rate limiting on sensitive endpoints
- Proper error message handling

## Testing Requirements

### 1. Unit Testing

- Jest for unit tests
- Test all utility functions
- Component testing with React Testing Library
- Minimum 80% code coverage

### 2. Integration Testing

- API endpoint testing
- Database operation testing
- Authentication flow testing

### 3. E2E Testing

